Author:  HILGENDORF
Vol / Page:  157
Edition:  1967
Quote:  TOAD FLAX (<i>Linaria [vulgaris]</i>), often called linaria, and sometimes yellow toad flax, is frequent on roadsides and waste land in both islands. It is [perennial] with trailing stems up to 30 inches long. ... Four other linarias, all called toad flax, and all with spurred flowers, are found in a few localities.
